children.text: The stair risers in this area has been constructed with openings greater than the allowable 125mm.
Part 3.9.1.2 Stairway construction of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘A stairway must have risers which do not have any openings that would allow a 125 mm sphere to pass through between the treads’;
These stair risers must be immediately rectified so that they meet the requirements of the BCA.
